Assuming all data fit into the L1 cache, each call to the function takes 7.20 cycles. At this rate:
 - 6% of peak load performance is reached (7.78 out of 128.00 bytes loaded per cycle (GB/s @ 1GHz))
 - 8% of peak store performance is reached (5.56 out of 64.00 bytes stored per cycle (GB/s @ 1GHz))

expert.title: Front-end bottlenecks
expert.txt:
Performance is limited by instruction throughput (loading/decoding program instructions to execution core) (front-end is a bottleneck).

By removing all these bottlenecks, you can lower the cost of an iteration from 7.20 to 6.00 cycles (1.20x speedup).
